def: Pertaining to the calcaneum; as, calcaneal arteries.
A genus of birds that comprises the white-eyes. See White-eye.
A false or erroneous trial; a trial which has no result.
A substance from the yolk of salmon's egg.
The doctrine of signs as the expression of thought orreasoning; the science of indicating thought by signs. Smart.
A small beaklike process or extension of some part; a smallrostrum; as, the rostellum of the stigma of violets, or of theoperculum of many mosses; the rostellum on the head of a tapeworm.
A small tree of the genus Citrus (C. Japonica) growing in Chinaand Japan; also, its small acid, orange-colored fruit used forpreserves.
